I've considered writing a tale from Ion's point of view. A man who sold out our world. A weak slave who started a rebellion in a part of the Daeva empire near the Ural mountains and people willing to sacrifice others in order to get ahead.

In my mind, as I tried to hint with other SCP, Ion and  (originally a city state ruled by the Daeva, now much more) was cast into another iteration of our world. And consumed it. He presents himself as almost like the pope of these cults but I think of him more as a middle-man, making terrible bargains with entities outside our reality - chaotic, Lovecraftian sort of horrors.

And now, with its various cults waiting, eagerly for their sorcerer-king, their perverted reality is bleeding back into ours. I don't think of Ion as human anymore. Or at least, its built a godlike presence around itself, carved from flesh and shaped by anomalous relics, to hide that formerly mortal core.





